    {
        "user": "USYQKE5HN",
        "type": "message",
        "ts": "1635601455.105000",
        "client_msg_id": "24FA63FD-6DFF-4189-892B-C620B6146DB2",
        "text": "I recommend you do a backtest to check if your close bet is costing you. Alternatively track it going forward, eg. with a different order tag. There’s a good chance you’ll win just as much or even more (gross) without that closing bet. The other benefit is that it’ll increase your comm gen naturally. \n\nOf course the trade off is that you’ll need to deal with much bigger returns variance. So when you backtest do it over as much data as you can to see what that would be like and if you can stomach it.\n\nAn alternative is a halfway house where you close only half your position - your close will only do half damage, variance is moderated, comm gen is still better than full close. ",
        "team": "T4G9NBD2M",
        "user_team": "T4G9NBD2M",
        "source_team": "T4G9NBD2M",
        "user_profile": {
